@@TJvDropTarget
<TITLEIMG TJvDropTarget>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.System, JVCL.FormsAndApp.Forms
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  Enables a control to accepts dropped files.
Description
  Use TJvDropTarget to enable a control to accept dropped files.

  To use a TJvDropTarget, do the following:

  * Drop a TJvDropTarget component on a form.
  * Set Control to the control that should accept dropped files.
  * Set property AcceptDrag to true; this means that now the control accepts dropped files.
  * Write an OnDragDrop event handler, that will respond when the user drops files on the    <LINK
     TJvDropTarget.Control,drop target>. Use the methods of the component in the event handle,
     to retrieve the file names, content etc. of the dropped files.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDropTarget.AcceptDrag
Summary
  Indicates whether the drop target accepts dropped files.
Description
  Set AcceptDrag to true to accept dropped files or set it to false to not accept dropped files.
See Also
  TJvDropTarget.Control

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDropTarget.Control
Summary
  The control that accept dragged content.
Description
  Set control to point to a control on your form to make that control accept dragged files. When a
  valid control is assigned and AcceptDrag is true, the cursor will turn into an accept cursor when
  it hovers above the control in a drag and drop action.,
See Also
  TJvDropTarget.AcceptDrag

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDropTarget.DataObject
Summary
  Pointer to the underlying Windows data object instance.
Description
  Use DataObject when you need to access the Windows IDataObject underlying the component. For
  example, this property might be necessary when call native API functions.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDropTarget.GetFileContent
Summary
  Saves the content of a dragged file to a stream.
Description
  Call GetFileContent when you need to retrieve the data of a dragged file.
Parameters
  Index  - The index of the file in the file list. Index must be between 0 and GetFileDescrCount - 1.
  Stream - The stream to save the content to.
Return value
  True if the data could be saved to the stream, false otherwise.
See Also
  TJvDropTarget.GetFileDescrCount, TJvDropTarget.GetFilenames

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDropTarget.GetFileDescrCount
Summary
  Returns the number of dropped files.
Description
  Call GetFileDescrCount to learn the number of files dropped.
Return value
  The number of files dropped

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDropTarget.GetFileDescrNames
Summary
  Retrieves the names of the dropped files.
Description
  Call GetFileDescrNames to fill a TStrings with the names of the dropped files. GetFileDescrNames is
  equivalent to GetFilenames but uses the DataObject to retrieve the names.
Parameters
  List - The list to save the filenames to.
Return value
  The number of items added to List.
See Also
  TJvDropTarget.GetFilenames

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDropTarget.GetFilenames
Summary
  Retrieves the names of the dropped files.
Description
  Call GetFilenames to fill a TStrings with the names of the dropped files. GetFilenames is
  equivalent to GetFileDescrNames but uses the HDROP handle to retrieve the names.
Parameters
  List - The list to save the filenames to.
Return value
  The number of items added to List.
See Also
  TJvDropTarget.GetFileDescrNames

